Figs. 15 –17, 19– 20
) small, blunt, with 2 setae, one long, thin, other minute; dorsal tubercles (d): i with minute seta, ii with medium-sized, stout seta; iii with long seta; iv with very long, thin seta, v small, minute seta ( Figs. 16, 21 ). Two ventrolateral (vl) long, thin setae (
Fig. 18
); 2 ventromedial (vm), mediumsized setae, one stouter (
Fig. 18
